{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_FdviVIYkfjrIAb3yzFOOFyQw","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Research Summary — TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n     2→\n     3→Status: warn\n     4→Last reviewed: 2026-03-18\n     5→Ticket: TST-001\n     6→Slug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\n     7→\n     8→## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK\n     9→- TBD\n    10→- Limit: <= 20 lines / <= 1200 chars.\n    11→- Paths discovered: none\n    12→- Invalid paths: none\n    13→- Pack-first: используйте `*-rlm.pack.*` и `rlm-slice`; не вставляйте raw JSONL.\n    14→\n    15→## AIDD:PRD_OVERRIDES\n    16→- none\n    17→## AIDD:NON_NEGOTIABLES\n    18→- All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs must enforce RBAC with 403 on violations\n    19→- Role operations (GRANT/REVOKE) must be auditable with timestamp, user, action\n    20→- Frontend role guards must update within 5 seconds of session change\n    21→- RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms\n    22→\n    23→## AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS\n    24→- Q1: Should RBAC be implemented as Spring Security filters or custom middleware? (Spring Security not currently in classpath)\n    25→- Q2: How to handle profile-to-role mapping given current header-based auth (no JWT)?\n    26→- Q3: Should WebSocket be introduced or extend existing SSE infrastructure for role sync?\n    27→\n    28→## AIDD:RISKS\n    29→| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n    30→|------|--------|------------|\n    31→| No Spring Security in current classpath | High | Add spring-boot-starter-security dependency |\n    32→| No JWT infrastructure exists | Medium | Implement custom RBAC based on profile roles from header |\n    33→| Profile auth uses custom headers not JWT claims | Medium | Adapt RBAC to use X-Profile-Key header for identity |\n    34→| SSE exists but PRD requires WebSocket | Low | Evaluate SSE for role push or implement WebSocket |\n    35→| Database schema has no audit_log table | Medium | Create new migration for audit_log table |\n    36→\n    37→## AIDD:DECISIONS\n    38→- **Auth Model**: Current system uses X-Profile-Key and X-Profile-Auth headers, not JWT\n    39→- **State Management**: Frontend uses Zustand (not Redux) with persistence\n    40→- **Real-time**: SSE already implemented for flows/MCP; WebSocket needs new infrastructure\n    41→- **Role Storage**: Roles stored in profile document (see profileTypes.ts: `roles: z.array(z.string())`)\n    42→\n    43→## AIDD:INTEGRATION_POINTS\n    44→\n    45→### Backend Integration Points\n    46→\n    47→1. **Profile Header Extraction** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts:92-110`)\n    48→   - `buildActiveProfileHeaders()` creates headers: X-Profile-Key, X-Profile-Channel, X-Profile-Auth\n    49→   - Backend must read these headers for identity\n    50→\n    51→2. **API Client** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts`)\n    52→   - All API calls use `buildActiveProfileHeaders()` for authentication\n    53→   - Admin role APIs: `fetchAdminProfiles()`, `assignProfileRole()`, `revokeProfileRole()`\n    54→\n    55→3. **No Existing Security Configuration**\n    56→   - No SecurityConfig, JWT, or @PreAuthorize annotations found\n    57→   - No spring-boot-starter-security in build.gradle\n    58→\n    59→### Frontend Integration Points\n    60→\n    61→1. **Profile Store** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`)\n    62→   - Uses Zustand with persistence\n    63→   - Profile document includes `roles: string[]`\n    64→   - Admin check: `state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin')`\n    65→\n    66→2. **Admin Role Guard** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx:34-36`)\n    67→   ```typescript\n    68→   const hasAdminRole = useProfileStore(\n    69→     (state) => !!state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin'),\n    70→   );\n    71→   ```\n    72→\n    73→3. **Route Guard** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/App.tsx:41-45`)\n    74→   ```typescript\n    75→   {hasAdminRole && (\n    76→     <NavLink to=\"/admin/roles\" className=\"nav-link\">\n    77→       Admin\n    78→     </NavLink>\n    79→   )}\n    80→   ```\n    81→\n    82→4. **SSE Infrastructure** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts`)\n    83→   - `subscribeToFlowEvents()` uses EventSource for real-time updates\n    84→   - Could be extended for role change notifications\n    85→\n    86→## AIDD:REUSE_CANDIDATES\n    87→\n    88→1. **Profile Header Parsing**\n    89→   - Location: `buildActiveProfileHeaders()` in `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts:92-110`\n    90→   - Reuse: Backend should implement similar header parsing for identity extraction\n    91→\n    92→2. **Role Check Pattern**\n    93→   - Location: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx:34-36`\n    94→   - Pattern: `state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin')`\n    95→   - Reuse: Standardize role check utility\n    96→\n    97→3. **Audit Event Types**\n    98→   - Location: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/components/ActiveProfileBanner.tsx:77-95`\n    99→   - Events: 'profile_created', 'profile_updated', 'identity_attached', 'identity_detached', 'role_assigned', 'role_revoked'\n   100→   - Reuse: Extend for RBAC audit events\n   101→\n   102→4. **SSE Event Handling**\n   103→   - Location: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/FlowSessions.tsx`\n   104→   - Pattern: EventSource with fallback to polling\n   105→   - Reuse: Adapt for role change push notifications\n   106→\n   107→## AIDD:COMMANDS_RUN\n   108→```bash\n   109→# Search for auth/security patterns\n   110→grep -r -i \"websocket\\|socket.io\\|sse\\|event-source\\|EventSource\" frontend/src/\n   111→grep -r -i \"jwt\\|spring-security\\|SecurityFilter\\|@PreAuthorize\\|@Secured\" backend-mcp/src/\n   112→grep -r -i \"role\\|permission\\|admin\\|RBAC\" backend-mcp/src/main/java/\n   113→\n   114→# File discovery\n   115→glob **/*Security*.java\n   116→glob **/*Auth*.java\n   117→glob **/*Config*.java\n   118→```\n   119→\n   120→## AIDD:RLM_EVIDENCE\n   121→- Status: warn\n   122→- Pack: aidd/reports/research/TST-001-rlm.pack.json\n   123→- Pack status: found\n   124→- Pack bytes: 11279\n   125→- Pack updated_at: 2026-03-18T09:44:42Z\n   126→- Warnings: rlm_links_empty_warn, rlm_links_empty_reason=no_symbols (e.g., rlm_links_empty_warn)\n   127→- Pending reason: rlm_links_empty_warn\n   128→- Next action: python3 ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/skills/aidd-rlm/runtime/rlm_links_build.py --ticket TST-001\n   129→- Baseline marker: links_empty_reason=no_symbols\n   130→- Auto recovery: auto_recovery_attempted=yes, bootstrap_attempted=yes, finalize_attempted=yes, recovery_path=bootstrap_nodes\n   131→- Slice: python3 ${CLAUDE_PLUGIN_ROOT}/skills/aidd-rlm/runtime/rlm_slice.py --ticket TST-001 --query \"<token>\"\n   132→- Nodes/links: aidd/reports/research/TST-001-rlm.nodes.jsonl / aidd/reports/research/TST-001-rlm.links.jsonl (не читать целиком)\n   133→\n   134→## AIDD:TEST_HOOKS\n   135→- Frontend tests: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.test.ts`\n   136→- No backend security tests found\n   137→- Suggested: Add RBAC middleware tests, audit logging tests\n   138→\n   139→## Context Pack (TL;DR)\n   140→- **Entry points**: Backend MCP server on port 8080 (configurable via profiles)\n   141→- **Reuse candidates**: Profile header auth, Zustand role checks, SSE infrastructure\n   142→- **Integration points**: X-Profile-Key header parsing, role assignment/revocation APIs\n   143→- **RLM**: No existing security patterns found (greenfield RBAC implementation)\n   144→- **Test pointers**: profileStore.test.ts for frontend state testing\n   145→- **Top risks**: No Spring Security, no JWT, custom auth model\n   146→\n   147→## Definition of reviewed\n   148→- [x] Найдены ≥ 1 точки интеграции или явно указан baseline\n   149→- [x] Указаны тесты/контракты или явно зафиксирован риск «нет тестов»\n   150→- [x] Зафиксированы команды/пути сканирования и ссылки на отчёты\n   151→\n   152→## Контекст\n   153→- **Цель фичи**: Implement live RBAC enforcement for all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and frontend sync\n   154→- **Scope изменений**: Backend middleware, audit database schema, frontend real-time sync\n   155→- **Ключевые модули/директории**:\n   156→  - Backend: `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/` - no security module exists\n   157→  - Frontend: `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`, `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx`\n   158→- **Исходные артефакты**: PRD TST-001, Context Pack TST-001\n   159→- **Логи команд / отчёты**: RLM worklist shows no existing security patterns\n   160→\n   161→## Точки интеграции\n   162→\n   163→### Backend\n   164→1. **New RBAC Middleware** (to be created)\n   165→   - Location: `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/security/`\n   166→   - Integration: Spring WebFlux filter chain (WebFlux already in classpath)\n   167→   - Headers to read: X-Profile-Key, X-Profile-Auth\n   168→\n   169→2. **Audit Log Table** (new migration needed)\n   170→   - Location: `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/`\n   171→   - Schema: timestamp, user_id (profile_key), action, target_resource, result\n   172→\n   173→3. **Profile Service Integration**\n   174→   - Current: Profile roles returned via API (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileTypes.ts:31`)\n   175→   - Integration: Backend needs to validate roles against profile service or cache\n   176→\n   177→### Frontend\n   178→1. **Profile Store Extension** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`)\n   179→   - Add: WebSocket/SSE listener for role changes\n   180→   - Current: `applyProfileSnapshot()` updates profile including roles (line 57-64)\n   181→\n   182→2. **API Client** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts`)\n   183→   - Already has: `subscribeToFlowEvents()` for SSE\n   184→   - Add: Role change subscription endpoint\n   185→\n   186→## Повторное использование\n   187→\n   188→### 1. Header-based Authentication\n   189→- **Path**: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts:92-110`\n   190→- **Usage**: Backend filter should parse X-Profile-Key header format: `{namespace}:{reference}`\n   191→- **Risk**: Custom auth not standardized; document contract clearly\n   192→- **Tests**: No existing tests for header parsing\n   193→\n   194→### 2. Zustand Role State Pattern\n   195→- **Path**: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx:34-36`\n   196→- **Usage**: `useProfileStore((state) => !!state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin'))`\n   197→- **Risk**: Role check scattered across components; create reusable hook\n   198→- **Tests**: Component-level tests needed\n   199→\n   200→### 3. SSE Infrastructure\n   201→- **Path**: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts` (subscribeToFlowEvents)\n   202→- **Usage**: Extend for role change notifications or implement WebSocket\n   203→- **Risk**: SSE is unidirectional; role changes may need bidirectional comms\n   204→- **Tests**: FlowSessions.tsx has SSE usage patterns\n   205→\n   206→## Принятые практики\n   207→- Profile headers: X-Profile-Key, X-Profile-Channel, X-Profile-Auth (see profileStore.ts)\n   208→- Role storage: Array of strings in profile document (profileTypes.ts:31)\n   209→- Audit events: Structured with eventType, metadata, timestamp (ActiveProfileBanner.tsx:77-95)\n   210→\n   211→## RLM evidence\n   212→- **No existing security modules found** - greenfield implementation required\n   213→- **Database entities exist**: NoteEntity with user_namespace/user_reference pattern\n   214→- **Header-based auth established**: X-Profile-Key pattern used across frontend\n   215→\n   216→## Паттерны/анти-паттерны\n   217→- **Паттерны**:\n   218→  - Header-based service-to-service auth (FlowOpsClientConfiguration.java:27-29)\n   219→  - Zod schema validation for API responses (apiClient.ts:187-194)\n   220→  - Audit event typing with metadata (profileTypes.ts:38-47)\n   221→- **Анти-паттерны**:\n   222→  - No centralized auth/authorization layer\n   223→  - Role checks inline in components (AdminRoles.tsx, App.tsx)\n   224→  - No standardized 403 handling\n   225→\n   226→## Отсутствие паттернов / отсутствующие данные\n   227→- **No Spring Security**: spring-boot-starter-security not in build.gradle\n   228→- **No JWT libraries**: No jjwt or similar dependencies\n   229→- **No @PreAuthorize annotations**: No method-level security\n   230→- **No WebSocket**: No spring-boot-starter-websocket\n   231→- **No audit_log table**: Only note_entry and repo_rag_* tables exist\n   232→\n   233→## Gap-анализ\n   234→\n   235→| Gap | Ограничение | Компенсационный шаг |\n   236→|-----|-------------|---------------------|\n   237→| No Spring Security | Must add dependency | Add spring-boot-starter-security to build.gradle |\n   238→| Custom header auth vs JWT | PRD assumes JWT claims | Adapt RBAC to extract roles from profile service using X-Profile-Key |\n   239→| No WebSocket | PRD requires WebSocket push | Evaluate SSE extension first (lower complexity) |\n   240→| No audit table | Need audit_log schema | Create Liquibase migration for audit_log table |\n   241→| Zustand vs Redux | PRD mentions Redux | Update PRD to reflect actual Zustand usage |\n   242→\n   243→## Следующие шаги\n   244→1. **Update PRD**: Change Q2 answer from JWT-claims to custom header-based auth\n   245→2. **Add Dependencies**: spring-boot-starter-security, spring-boot-starter-websocket (if WebSocket chosen)\n   246→3. **Create Database Migration**: audit_log table with Liquibase\n   247→4. **Implement RBAC Filter**: Spring WebFlux filter for POST/PUT/DELETE endpoints\n   248→5. **Extend Profile Store**: Add real-time role sync (SSE or WebSocket)\n   249→6. **Create Audit Service**: Log GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED operations\n   250→\n   251→## Дополнительные заметки\n   252→\n   253→### Current Database Schema (PostgreSQL)\n   254→- **Existing tables**: note_entry, note_vector_store, repo_rag_*\n   255→- **Pattern**: UUID primary keys, JSONB for metadata, created_at/updated_at timestamps\n   256→- **User identification**: user_namespace + user_reference (see NoteEntity.java:40-44)\n   257→\n   258→### Frontend Dependencies\n   259→- **State**: Zustand (not Redux)\n   260→- **HTTP**: Native fetch\n   261→- **Validation**: Zod\n   262→- **Real-time**: EventSource (SSE) for flows\n   263→\n   264→### Backend Dependencies (build.gradle)\n   265→- **Web**: spring-boot-starter-webflux\n   266→- **Data**: spring-boot-starter-data-jpa, postgresql\n   267→- **No security**: spring-boot-starter-security missing\n   268→- **No WebSocket**: spring-boot-starter-websocket missing\n   269→\n   270→### Profile API Contract\n   271→- **Headers**: X-Profile-Key (format: `namespace:reference`), X-Profile-Auth (dev token)\n   272→- **Role format**: Array of strings (`roles: [\"admin\", \"user\"]`)\n   273→- **Admin check**: Presence of `\"admin\"` in roles array\n   274→\n   275→## Открытые вопросы\n   276→1. **Q1**: Should we add Spring Security or implement custom WebFlux filters for RBAC?\n   277→2. **Q2**: Should we use existing SSE or implement WebSocket for role sync?\n   278→3. **Q3**: How should backend fetch profile roles? Cache or call profile service on each request?\n   279→4. **Q4**: What is the source of truth for roles? Profile service or local RBAC tables?\n   280→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"tool_EkXO8SVVEnKyCVtVN2wxMhSx","session_id":"c9d8f772-fac0-4aa0-ba05-6715d2bcaffd","uuid":"b5221538-3914-497b-99bd-e45d2da16fd8"}
