{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_XFgNJqNoW9dHB40jMtbASoyh","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Implementation Plan — TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n     2→\n     3→**Status:** READY\n     4→**Ticket:** TST-001\n     5→**Updated:** 2026-03-18\n     6→**Research Status:** warn (see research findings for PRD overrides)\n     7→\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→## Executive Summary\n    11→\n    12→This plan implements live RBAC enforcement for all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) with audit logging and frontend role synchronization. Based on research findings, we adapt the PRD assumptions to the actual codebase:\n    13→\n    14→| PRD Assumption | Research Finding | Adaptation |\n    15→|----------------|------------------|------------|\n    16→| JWT claims auth | X-Profile-Key header auth | Custom WebFlux filter with header parsing |\n    17→| Redux state | Zustand with persistence | Extend Zustand store with SSE listener |\n    18→| WebSocket push | SSE already exists for flows | Extend SSE for role notifications |\n    19→| Spring Security | Not in classpath | Custom WebFlux filters (no Spring Security) |\n    20→\n    21→---\n    22→\n    23→## AIDD:DECISIONS\n    24→\n    25→### Architecture Decisions\n    26→\n    27→1. **No Spring Security** — Adding spring-boot-starter-security introduces significant complexity and potential conflicts with existing WebFlux setup. Instead, implement custom `WebFilter` for RBAC.\n    28→\n    29→2. **Extend SSE instead of WebSocket** — SSE infrastructure already exists (`subscribeToFlowEvents` in apiClient.ts). Adding WebSocket requires new dependencies and infrastructure. SSE is sufficient for unidirectional server-to-client role updates.\n    30→\n    31→3. **Role Caching with Caffeine** — Backend uses Caffeine cache (already in classpath). Cache profile roles with 5-minute TTL to meet P95 ≤ 10ms latency requirement.\n    32→\n    33→4. **Audit Log as Separate Table** — Follow existing pattern (note_entry table) with PostgreSQL JSONB for flexible metadata.\n    34→\n    35→5. **Header-Based Identity** — Use `X-Profile-Key` (format: `namespace:reference`) and `X-Profile-Auth` headers for identity extraction.\n    36→\n    37→---\n    38→\n    39→## AIDD:NON_NEGOTIABLES\n    40→\n    41→- All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs must return 403 for unauthorized requests\n    42→- Audit log must capture: timestamp, actor profile key, action (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED), target resource, result\n    43→- Frontend role guards must update within 5 seconds of backend role change\n    44→- RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms\n    45→- Zero breaking changes to existing API contracts\n    46→\n    47→---\n    48→\n    49→## AIDD:RISKS\n    50→\n    51→| Risk ID | Description | Probability | Impact | Mitigation |\n    52→|---------|-------------|-------------|--------|------------|\n    53→| R-001 | Profile service unavailable | Medium | High | Circuit breaker; fail-closed; cache roles |\n    54→| R-002 | Cache stale roles after assignment | Medium | Medium | Cache invalidation on role change; TTL 5min |\n    55→| R-003 | SSE connection memory leak | Low | Medium | Proper cleanup on disconnect; subscriber limits |\n    56→| R-004 | Audit log write failures | Low | Medium | Async logging; error queue; never block request |\n    57→| R-005 | RBAC filter performance degradation | Low | High | Caffeine cache; async audit; P95 target 10ms |\n    58→| R-006 | Breaking change to existing APIs | Low | High | Feature flags; audit-only mode first; rollback |\n    59→| R-007 | Component scan misses RBAC beans | Medium | High | Add to all profile configs; verify on startup |\n    60→| R-008 | Missing profile service integration | High | High | Define contract; implement fallback to local DB |\n    61→\n    62→### Validation-Derived Risks (from TST-001-validation.md)\n    63→\n    64→**R-007: Component Scan Configuration**\n    65→The application uses profile-based component scanning. The RBAC module needs to be added to ALL profiles or a shared configuration created.\n    66→- **Mitigation**: Create `RbacConfig.java` with `@Profile(\"!test\")` active in all non-test profiles\n    67→\n    68→**R-008: Profile Service Integration**\n    69→The plan assumes `profileClient.fetchRoles()` exists, but no backend API for fetching profile roles was found in research.\n    70→- **Mitigation**: Define profile service contract or implement local role storage via `rbac_profile_roles` table\n    71→\n    72→---\n    73→\n    74→## Milestones & Iterations\n    75→\n    76→### Phase 1: Backend Foundation (Days 1-3)\n    77→**Goal:** Core RBAC filter and audit infrastructure\n    78→\n    79→#### 1.1 Database Migration\n    80→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml`\n    81→\n    82→```yaml\n    83→# Create audit_log table\n    84→- changeSet:\n    85→    id: rbac-0001-audit-log\n    86→    author: ai-advent\n    87→    context: rbac\n    88→    changes:\n    89→      - createTable:\n    90→          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n    91→          columns:\n    92→            - column:\n    93→                name: id\n    94→                type: UUID\n    95→                defaultValueComputed: gen_random_uuid()\n    96→                constraints:\n    97→                  primaryKey: true\n    98→            - column:\n    99→                name: timestamp\n   100→                type: TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE\n   101→                defaultValueComputed: now()\n   102→                constraints:\n   103→                  nullable: false\n   104→            - column:\n   105→                name: actor_namespace\n   106→                type: VARCHAR(32)\n   107→                constraints:\n   108→                  nullable: false\n   109→            - column:\n   110→                name: actor_reference\n   111→                type: VARCHAR(128)\n   112→                constraints:\n   113→                  nullable: false\n   114→            - column:\n   115→                name: action\n   116→                type: VARCHAR(32)\n   117→                constraints:\n   118→                  nullable: false\n   119→            - column:\n   120→                name: target_resource\n   121→                type: VARCHAR(256)\n   122→            - column:\n   123→                name: target_profile_namespace\n   124→                type: VARCHAR(32)\n   125→            - column:\n   126→                name: target_profile_reference\n   127→                type: VARCHAR(128)\n   128→            - column:\n   129→                name: result\n   130→                type: VARCHAR(16)\n   131→                constraints:\n   132→                  nullable: false\n   133→            - column:\n   134→                name: http_method\n   135→                type: VARCHAR(8)\n   136→            - column:\n   137→                name: http_path\n   138→                type: VARCHAR(512)\n   139→            - column:\n   140→                name: metadata\n   141→                type: JSONB\n   142→      - createIndex:\n   143→          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n   144→          indexName: idx_rbac_audit_timestamp\n   145→          columns:\n   146→            - column:\n   147→                name: timestamp\n   148→      - createIndex:\n   149→          tableName: rbac_audit_log\n   150→          indexName: idx_rbac_audit_actor\n   151→          columns:\n   152→            - column:\n   153→                name: actor_namespace\n   154→            - column:\n   155→                name: actor_reference\n   156→```\n   157→\n   158→#### 1.2 RBAC Core Domain\n   159→**Files to create:**\n   160→\n   161→| File | Purpose |\n   162→|------|---------|\n   163→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Role.java` | Enum: ADMIN, USER, VIEWER, etc. |\n   164→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentity.java` | Value object: namespace + reference |\n   165→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Permission.java` | Enum: READ, WRITE, DELETE, ADMIN |\n   166→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RbacDecision.java` | Record: allowed (boolean), reason (string) |\n   167→\n   168→#### 1.3 RBAC Filter (WebFlux)\n   169→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilter.java`\n   170→\n   171→```java\n   172→@Component\n   173→@Order(Ordered.HIGHEST_PRECEDENCE + 100) // After logging, before business logic\n   174→public class RbacWebFilter implements WebFilter {\n   175→\n   176→    private final ProfileRoleService roleService;\n   177→    private final AuditLogService auditService;\n   178→    private final RbacPathMatcher pathMatcher;\n   179→\n   180→    @Override\n   181→    public Mono<Void> filter(ServerWebExchange exchange, WebFilterChain chain) {\n   182→        HttpMethod method = exchange.getRequest().getMethod();\n   183→        String path = exchange.getRequest().getPath().value();\n   184→\n   185→        // Skip non-mutation methods\n   186→        if (!isMutationMethod(method)) {\n   187→            return chain.filter(exchange);\n   188→        }\n   189→\n   190→        // Skip excluded paths (health, public APIs)\n   191→        if (pathMatcher.isPublicPath(path)) {\n   192→            return chain.filter(exchange);\n   193→        }\n   194→\n   195→        // Extract identity from headers\n   196→        ProfileIdentity identity = extractIdentity(exchange.getRequest());\n   197→        if (identity == null) {\n   198→            return auditAndDeny(exchange, null, path, method, \"Missing identity headers\");\n   199→        }\n   200→\n   201→        // Check required roles for path\n   202→        Set<Role> requiredRoles = pathMatcher.getRequiredRoles(path, method);\n   203→\n   204→        return roleService.hasAnyRole(identity, requiredRoles)\n   205→            .flatMap(hasRole -> {\n   206→                if (hasRole) {\n   207→                    auditService.logAccess(identity, path, method, \"ALLOWED\");\n   208→                    return chain.filter(exchange);\n   209→                } else {\n   210→                    return auditAndDeny(exchange, identity, path, method, \"Insufficient permissions\");\n   211→                }\n   212→            })\n   213→            .onErrorResume(e -> {\n   214→                log.error(\"RBAC check failed\", e);\n   215→                return auditAndDeny(exchange, identity, path, method, \"RBAC error: \" + e.getMessage());\n   216→            });\n   217→    }\n   218→\n   219→    private Mono<Void> auditAndDeny(ServerWebExchange exchange, ProfileIdentity identity,\n   220→                                     String path, HttpMethod method, String reason) {\n   221→        auditService.logDenied(identity, path, method, reason);\n   222→        exchange.getResponse().setStatusCode(HttpStatus.FORBIDDEN);\n   223→        exchange.getResponse().getHeaders().setContentType(MediaType.APPLICATION_JSON);\n   224→        String body = String.format(\"{\\\"error\\\":\\\"Forbidden\\\",\\\"reason\\\":\\\"%s\\\"}\", reason);\n   225→        DataBuffer buffer = exchange.getResponse().bufferFactory().wrap(body.getBytes());\n   226→        return exchange.getResponse().writeWith(Mono.just(buffer));\n   227→    }\n   228→}\n   229→```\n   230→\n   231→#### 1.4 Profile Role Service with Caching\n   232→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleService.java`\n   233→\n   234→```java\n   235→@Service\n   236→public class ProfileRoleService {\n   237→\n   238→    private final LoadingCache<ProfileIdentity, Set<Role>> roleCache;\n   239→    private final ProfileClient profileClient;\n   240→\n   241→    public ProfileRoleService(ProfileClient profileClient,\n   242→                              @Value(\"${rbac.cache.ttl-minutes:5}\") int cacheTtlMinutes) {\n   243→        this.profileClient = profileClient;\n   244→        this.roleCache = Caffeine.newBuilder()\n   245→            .expireAfterWrite(cacheTtlMinutes, TimeUnit.MINUTES)\n   246→            .maximumSize(10_000)\n   247→            .recordStats()\n   248→            .build(this::loadRoles);\n   249→    }\n   250→\n   251→    private Set<Role> loadRoles(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n   252→        return profileClient.fetchRoles(identity);\n   253→    }\n   254→\n   255→    public Mono<Boolean> hasAnyRole(ProfileIdentity identity, Set<Role> requiredRoles) {\n   256→        if (requiredRoles.isEmpty()) {\n   257→            return Mono.just(true);\n   258→        }\n   259→        return Mono.fromCallable(() -> roleCache.get(identity))\n   260→            .subscribeOn(Schedulers.boundedElastic())\n   261→            .map(userRoles -> userRoles.stream().anyMatch(requiredRoles::contains));\n   262→    }\n   263→\n   264→    public void invalidateCache(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n   265→        roleCache.invalidate(identity);\n   266→    }\n   267→\n   268→    public CacheStats getCacheStats() {\n   269→        return roleCache.stats();\n   270→    }\n   271→}\n   272→```\n   273→\n   274→#### 1.5 Audit Log Service\n   275→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/AuditLogService.java`\n   276→\n   277→```java\n   278→@Service\n   279→public class AuditLogService {\n   280→\n   281→    private final AuditLogRepository repository;\n   282→    private final ExecutorService asyncExecutor = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(4);\n   283→\n   284→    public void logAccess(ProfileIdentity identity, String path, HttpMethod method, String result) {\n   285→        asyncLog(() -> {\n   286→            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n   287→            entry.setActorNamespace(identity.namespace());\n   288→            entry.setActorReference(identity.reference());\n   289→            entry.setAction(\"ACCESS\");\n   290→            entry.setTargetResource(path);\n   291→            entry.setHttpMethod(method.name());\n   292→            entry.setHttpPath(path);\n   293→            entry.setResult(result);\n   294→            repository.save(entry);\n   295→        });\n   296→    }\n   297→\n   298→    public void logDenied(ProfileIdentity identity, String path, HttpMethod method, String reason) {\n   299→        asyncLog(() -> {\n   300→            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n   301→            if (identity != null) {\n   302→                entry.setActorNamespace(identity.namespace());\n   303→                entry.setActorReference(identity.reference());\n   304→            }\n   305→            entry.setAction(\"DENIED\");\n   306→            entry.setTargetResource(path);\n   307→            entry.setHttpMethod(method.name());\n   308→            entry.setHttpPath(path);\n   309→            entry.setResult(\"DENIED\");\n   310→            entry.setMetadata(Map.of(\"reason\", reason));\n   311→            repository.save(entry);\n   312→        });\n   313→    }\n   314→\n   315→    public void logRoleChange(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target,\n   316→                              String action, Set<Role> roles) {\n   317→        asyncLog(() -> {\n   318→            AuditLogEntry entry = new AuditLogEntry();\n   319→            entry.setActorNamespace(actor.namespace());\n   320→            entry.setActorReference(actor.reference());\n   321→            entry.setAction(action); // GRANT or REVOKE\n   322→            entry.setTargetProfileNamespace(target.namespace());\n   323→            entry.setTargetProfileReference(target.reference());\n   324→            entry.setResult(\"SUCCESS\");\n   325→            entry.setMetadata(Map.of(\"roles\", roles));\n   326→            repository.save(entry);\n   327→        });\n   328→    }\n   329→\n   330→    private void asyncLog(Runnable task) {\n   331→        asyncExecutor.submit(() -> {\n   332→            try {\n   333→                task.run();\n   334→            } catch (Exception e) {\n   335→                log.error(\"Failed to write audit log\", e);\n   336→            }\n   337→        });\n   338→    }\n   339→}\n   340→```\n   341→\n   342→#### 1.6 Audit Log Entity & Repository\n   343→**Files:**\n   344→- `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogEntity.java`\n   345→- `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepository.java`\n   346→\n   347→---\n   348→\n   349→### Phase 2: Profile Service Integration (Days 4-5)\n   350→**Goal:** Connect to existing profile service for role resolution\n   351→\n   352→#### 2.1 Profile Client\n   353→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileClient.java`\n   354→\n   355→```java\n   356→@Component\n   357→public class ProfileClient {\n   358→\n   359→    private final WebClient webClient;\n   360→    private final String profileServiceUrl;\n   361→\n   362→    public ProfileClient(@Value(\"${profile.service.url}\") String profileServiceUrl,\n   363→                         WebClient.Builder webClientBuilder) {\n   364→        this.profileServiceUrl = profileServiceUrl;\n   365→        this.webClient = webClientBuilder.baseUrl(profileServiceUrl).build();\n   366→    }\n   367→\n   368→    public Set<Role> fetchRoles(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n   369→        try {\n   370→            ProfileResponse response = webClient.get()\n   371→                .uri(\"/api/profiles/{namespace}/{reference}\", identity.namespace(), identity.reference())\n   372→                .retrieve()\n   373→                .bodyToMono(ProfileResponse.class)\n   374→                .timeout(Duration.ofSeconds(2))\n   375→                .block();\n   376→\n   377→            return response != null && response.roles() != null\n   378→                ? response.roles().stream().map(Role::valueOf).collect(Collectors.toSet())\n   379→                : Set.of();\n   380→        } catch (Exception e) {\n   381→            log.error(\"Failed to fetch roles for {}\", identity, e);\n   382→            // Fail-closed: return empty set (deny access)\n   383→            return Set.of();\n   384→        }\n   385→    }\n   386→}\n   387→```\n   388→\n   389→#### 2.2 Profile Response DTO\n   390→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileResponse.java`\n   391→\n   392→```java\n   393→public record ProfileResponse(\n   394→    String profileId,\n   395→    String namespace,\n   396→    String reference,\n   397→    List<String> roles,\n   398→    Instant updatedAt\n   399→) {}\n   400→```\n   401→\n   402→#### 2.3 RBAC Configuration\n   403→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacConfiguration.java`\n   404→\n   405→```java\n   406→@Configuration\n   407→@EnableConfigurationProperties(RbacProperties.class)\n   408→public class RbacConfiguration {\n   409→\n   410→    @Bean\n   411→    public RbacPathMatcher rbacPathMatcher(RbacProperties properties) {\n   412→        return new RbacPathMatcher(properties);\n   413→    }\n   414→}\n   415→```\n   416→\n   417→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacProperties.java`\n   418→\n   419→```java\n   420→@ConfigurationProperties(prefix = \"rbac\")\n   421→public record RbacProperties(\n   422→    List<PathRule> protectedPaths,\n   423→    List<String> publicPaths,\n   424→    int cacheTtlMinutes\n   425→) {\n   426→    public record PathRule(\n   427→        String path,\n   428→        Set<String> methods,\n   429→        Set<String> requiredRoles\n   430→    ) {}\n   431→}\n   432→```\n   433→\n   434→---\n   435→\n   436→### Phase 3: Frontend Role Sync (Days 6-8)\n   437→**Goal:** Real-time role synchronization via SSE\n   438→\n   439→#### 3.1 Extend Profile Store with SSE\n   440→**File:** `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` (modifications)\n   441→\n   442→```typescript\n   443→// Add to ProfileStoreState\n   444→type ProfileStoreState = {\n   445→  // ... existing fields\n   446→  roleVersion: number; // Incremented on role change\n   447→  lastRoleSync: string | null;\n   448→  subscribeToRoleChanges: () => () => void;\n   449→};\n   450→\n   451→// Add to store implementation\n   452→export const useProfileStore = create<ProfileStoreState>()(\n   453→  persist(\n   454→    (set, get) => ({\n   455→      // ... existing initial state\n   456→      roleVersion: 0,\n   457→      lastRoleSync: null,\n   458→\n   459→      subscribeToRoleChanges: () => {\n   460→        const { namespace, reference, channel, devToken } = getActiveProfileSelection();\n   461→        if (!namespace || !reference) return () => {};\n   462→\n   463→        const params = new URLSearchParams();\n   464→        params.set('namespace', namespace);\n   465→        params.set('reference', reference);\n   466→        if (channel) params.set('channel', channel);\n   467→        if (devToken) params.set('token', devToken);\n   468→\n   469→        const eventSource = new EventSource(\n   470→          `${API_BASE_URL}/api/profiles/role-events?${params.toString()}`\n   471→        );\n   472→\n   473→        eventSource.addEventListener('role-change', (event) => {\n   474→          const data = JSON.parse(event.data);\n   475→          set((state) => ({\n   476→            profile: state.profile ? {\n   477→              ...state.profile,\n   478→              roles: data.roles,\n   479→              updatedAt: data.timestamp,\n   480→            } : null,\n   481→            roleVersion: state.roleVersion + 1,\n   482→            lastRoleSync: new Date().toISOString(),\n   483→          }));\n   484→        });\n   485→\n   486→        eventSource.onerror = () => {\n   487→          // Auto-reconnect handled by browser, but we log it\n   488→          console.warn('Role events connection error, will retry...');\n   489→        };\n   490→\n   491→        return () => eventSource.close();\n   492→      },\n   493→    }),\n   494→    // ... existing persist config\n   495→  ),\n   496→);\n   497→```\n   498→\n   499→#### 3.2 Create useRoleGuard Hook\n   500→**File:** `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` (new)\n   501→\n   502→```typescript\n   503→import { useEffect, useMemo } from 'react';\n   504→import { useProfileStore } from './profileStore';\n   505→\n   506→export function useRoleGuard(requiredRole?: string) {\n   507→  const roles = useProfileStore((state) => state.profile?.roles ?? []);\n   508→  const roleVersion = useProfileStore((state) => state.roleVersion);\n   509→\n   510→  // Subscribe to role changes on mount\n   511→  useEffect(() => {\n   512→    const unsubscribe = useProfileStore.getState().subscribeToRoleChanges();\n   513→    return unsubscribe;\n   514→  }, []);\n   515→\n   516→  const hasRole = useMemo(() => {\n   517→    if (!requiredRole) return true;\n   518→    return roles.some((role) => role === requiredRole);\n   519→  }, [roles, requiredRole, roleVersion]);\n   520→\n   521→  const hasAnyRole = useMemo(() => {\n   522→    return (roleCodes: string[]) => roles.some((role) => roleCodes.includes(role));\n   523→  }, [roles, roleVersion]);\n   524→\n   525→  const hasAllRoles = useMemo(() => {\n   526→    return (roleCodes: string[]) => roleCodes.every((role) => roles.includes(role));\n   527→  }, [roles, roleVersion]);\n   528→\n   529→  return {\n   530→    roles,\n   531→    hasRole,\n   532→    hasAnyRole,\n   533→    hasAllRoles,\n   534→    isAdmin: roles.includes('admin'),\n   535→    roleVersion,\n   536→  };\n   537→}\n   538→```\n   539→\n   540→#### 3.3 Update AdminRoles Page\n   541→**File:** `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` (refactor)\n   542→\n   543→Replace inline role check with hook:\n   544→\n   545→```typescript\n   546→// Replace lines 34-36:\n   547→const { isAdmin } = useRoleGuard('admin');\n   548→\n   549→// Replace hasAdminRole references with isAdmin\n   550→```\n   551→\n   552→#### 3.4 Create RoleGuard Component\n   553→**File:** `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` (new)\n   554→\n   555→```typescript\n   556→import React from 'react';\n   557→import { useRoleGuard } from '../lib/useRoleGuard';\n   558→\n   559→interface RoleGuardProps {\n   560→  requiredRole: string;\n   561→  fallback?: React.ReactNode;\n   562→  children: React.ReactNode;\n   563→}\n   564→\n   565→export const RoleGuard: React.FC<RoleGuardProps> = ({\n   566→  requiredRole,\n   567→  fallback = null,\n   568→  children,\n   569→}) => {\n   570→  const { hasRole } = useRoleGuard(requiredRole);\n   571→  return hasRole ? <>{children}</> : <>{fallback}</>;\n   572→};\n   573→\n   574→interface AdminGuardProps {\n   575→  fallback?: React.ReactNode;\n   576→  children: React.ReactNode;\n   577→}\n   578→\n   579→export const AdminGuard: React.FC<AdminGuardProps> = ({ fallback, children }) => (\n   580→  <RoleGuard requiredRole=\"admin\" fallback={fallback}>\n   581→    {children}\n   582→  </RoleGuard>\n   583→);\n   584→```\n   585→\n   586→---\n   587→\n   588→### Phase 4: SSE Role Events Endpoint (Days 9-10)\n   589→**Goal:** Backend SSE endpoint for role change notifications\n   590→\n   591→#### 4.1 Role Event Service\n   592→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java`\n   593→\n   594→```java\n   595→@Service\n   596→public class RoleEventService {\n   597→\n   598→    private final Map<ProfileIdentity, Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent>> subscribers = new ConcurrentHashMap<>();\n   599→\n   600→    public Flux<RoleChangeEvent> subscribe(ProfileIdentity identity) {\n   601→        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = Sinks.many().multicast().onBackpressureBuffer();\n   602→        subscribers.put(identity, sink);\n   603→\n   604→        return sink.asFlux()\n   605→            .doOnCancel(() -> subscribers.remove(identity))\n   606→            .doOnTerminate(() -> subscribers.remove(identity));\n   607→    }\n   608→\n   609→    public void notifyRoleChange(ProfileIdentity identity, List<String> roles) {\n   610→        Sinks.Many<RoleChangeEvent> sink = subscribers.get(identity);\n   611→        if (sink != null) {\n   612→            sink.tryEmitNext(new RoleChangeEvent(roles, Instant.now()));\n   613→        }\n   614→    }\n   615→\n   616→    public void broadcastRoleChange(ProfileIdentity target, List<String> roles) {\n   617→        notifyRoleChange(target, roles);\n   618→    }\n   619→\n   620→    public record RoleChangeEvent(List<String> roles, Instant timestamp) {}\n   621→}\n   622→```\n   623→\n   624→#### 4.2 SSE Controller\n   625→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java`\n   626→\n   627→```java\n   628→@RestController\n   629→@RequestMapping(\"/api/profiles\")\n   630→public class RoleEventsController {\n   631→\n   632→    private final RoleEventService eventService;\n   633→\n   634→    @GetMapping(value = \"/role-events\", produces = MediaType.TEXT_EVENT_STREAM_VALUE)\n   635→    public Flux<ServerSentEvent<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>> roleEvents(\n   636→            @RequestParam String namespace,\n   637→            @RequestParam String reference,\n   638→            @RequestParam(required = false) String channel,\n   639→            @RequestParam(required = false) String token) {\n   640→\n   641→        ProfileIdentity identity = new ProfileIdentity(namespace, reference);\n   642→\n   643→        return eventService.subscribe(identity)\n   644→            .map(event -> ServerSentEvent.builder(event)\n   645→                .event(\"role-change\")\n   646→                .id(UUID.randomUUID().toString())\n   647→                .build())\n   648→            .mergeWith(heartbeatFlux());\n   649→    }\n   650→\n   651→    private Flux<ServerSentEvent<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>> heartbeatFlux() {\n   652→        return Flux.interval(Duration.ofSeconds(30))\n   653→            .map(i -> ServerSentEvent.<RoleEventService.RoleChangeEvent>builder()\n   654→                .comment(\"heartbeat\")\n   655→                .build());\n   656→    }\n   657→}\n   658→```\n   659→\n   660→#### 4.3 Integrate with Admin Role Operations\n   661→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleAssignmentService.java`\n   662→\n   663→```java\n   664→@Service\n   665→public class RoleAssignmentService {\n   666→\n   667→    private final ProfileClient profileClient;\n   668→    private final RoleEventService eventService;\n   669→    private final AuditLogService auditService;\n   670→    private final ProfileRoleService roleService;\n   671→\n   672→    public Mono<Void> assignRole(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target, Role role) {\n   673→        return profileClient.assignRole(target, role)\n   674→            .doOnSuccess(v -> {\n   675→                // Invalidate cache\n   676→                roleService.invalidateCache(target);\n   677→                // Notify user\n   678→                profileClient.fetchRoles(target)\n   679→                    .thenAccept(roles -> eventService.broadcastRoleChange(target, new ArrayList<>(roles)));\n   680→                // Audit\n   681→                auditService.logRoleChange(actor, target, \"GRANT\", Set.of(role));\n   682→            });\n   683→    }\n   684→\n   685→    public Mono<Void> revokeRole(ProfileIdentity actor, ProfileIdentity target, Role role) {\n   686→        return profileClient.revokeRole(target, role)\n   687→            .doOnSuccess(v -> {\n   688→                roleService.invalidateCache(target);\n   689→                profileClient.fetchRoles(target)\n   690→                    .thenAccept(roles -> eventService.broadcastRoleChange(target, new ArrayList<>(roles)));\n   691→                auditService.logRoleChange(actor, target, \"REVOKE\", Set.of(role));\n   692→            });\n   693→    }\n   694→}\n   695→```\n   696→\n   697→---\n   698→\n   699→### Phase 5: Testing & Validation (Days 11-12)\n   700→**Goal:** Comprehensive test coverage\n   701→\n   702→#### 5.1 Backend Tests\n   703→\n   704→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilterTest.java`\n   705→\n   706→```java\n   707→@WebFluxTest(RbacWebFilter.class)\n   708→class RbacWebFilterTest {\n   709→\n   710→    @MockBean\n   711→    private ProfileRoleService roleService;\n   712→\n   713→    @MockBean\n   714→    private AuditLogService auditService;\n   715→\n   716→    @Autowired\n   717→    private WebTestClient webClient;\n   718→\n   719→    @Test\n   720→    void shouldAllowGetRequestWithoutRole() {\n   721→        webClient.get().uri(\"/api/test\")\n   722→            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:test\")\n   723→            .exchange()\n   724→            .expectStatus().isOk();\n   725→    }\n   726→\n   727→    @Test\n   728→    void shouldDenyPostWithoutRole() {\n   729→        when(roleService.hasAnyRole(any(), any())).thenReturn(Mono.just(false));\n   730→\n   731→        webClient.post().uri(\"/api/test\")\n   732→            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:test\")\n   733→            .exchange()\n   734→            .expectStatus().isForbidden();\n   735→\n   736→        verify(auditService).logDenied(any(), eq(\"/api/test\"), eq(HttpMethod.POST), any());\n   737→    }\n   738→\n   739→    @Test\n   740→    void shouldAllowPostWithAdminRole() {\n   741→        when(roleService.hasAnyRole(any(), any())).thenReturn(Mono.just(true));\n   742→\n   743→        webClient.post().uri(\"/api/test\")\n   744→            .header(\"X-Profile-Key\", \"web:admin\")\n   745→            .exchange()\n   746→            .expectStatus().isOk();\n   747→    }\n   748→}\n   749→```\n   750→\n   751→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleServiceTest.java`\n   752→\n   753→```java\n   754→class ProfileRoleServiceTest {\n   755→\n   756→    @Test\n   757→    void shouldCacheRoles() {\n   758→        // First call hits profile service\n   759→        // Second call uses cache\n   760→        // Verify cache stats\n   761→    }\n   762→\n   763→    @Test\n   764→    void shouldFailClosedOnError() {\n   765→        // When profile service unavailable\n   766→        // Return empty roles (deny access)\n   767→    }\n   768→}\n   769→```\n   770→\n   771→#### 5.2 Frontend Tests\n   772→\n   773→**File:** `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.test.ts` (new)\n   774→\n   775→```typescript\n   776→import { renderHook, waitFor } from '@testing-library/react';\n   777→import { useRoleGuard } from './useRoleGuard';\n   778→import { useProfileStore } from './profileStore';\n   779→\n   780→describe('useRoleGuard', () => {\n   781→  it('should update when roles change', async () => {\n   782→    const { result } = renderHook(() => useRoleGuard('admin'));\n   783→\n   784→    expect(result.current.hasRole).toBe(false);\n   785→\n   786→    // Simulate role change event\n   787→    useProfileStore.setState({\n   788→      profile: { roles: ['admin'] } as UserProfileDocument,\n   789→      roleVersion: 1,\n   790→    });\n   791→\n   792→    await waitFor(() => {\n   793→      expect(result.current.hasRole).toBe(true);\n   794→    });\n   795→  });\n   796→});\n   797→```\n   798→\n   799→#### 5.3 Integration Tests\n   800→\n   801→**File:** `backend-mcp/src/test/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/RbacIntegrationTest.java`\n   802→\n   803→```java\n   804→@SpringBootTest(webEnvironment = SpringBootTest.WebEnvironment.RANDOM_PORT)\n   805→class RbacIntegrationTest {\n   806→\n   807→    @Test\n   808→    void endToEndRoleChangeFlow() {\n   809→        // 1. User with viewer role tries POST -> 403\n   810→        // 2. Admin assigns write role\n   811→        // 3. User receives SSE notification\n   812→        // 4. User retries POST -> 200\n   813→        // 5. Audit log contains both DENIED and ALLOWED entries\n   814→    }\n   815→}\n   816→```\n   817→\n   818→#### 5.4 Performance Tests\n   819→\n   820→```java\n   821→@Test\n   822→void rbacLatencyP95Under10ms() {\n   823→    // Run 1000 requests\n   824→    // Measure RBAC check time\n   825→    // Assert P95 < 10ms\n   826→}\n   827→```\n   828→\n   829→---\n   830→\n   831→## Files to Create/Modify\n   832→\n   833→### New Files (Backend)\n   834→\n   835→| Path | Purpose |\n   836→|------|---------|\n   837→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Role.java` | Role enum |\n   838→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/ProfileIdentity.java` | Identity VO |\n   839→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/Permission.java` | Permission enum |\n   840→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/domain/RbacDecision.java` | Decision record |\n   841→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/filter/RbacWebFilter.java` | Main RBAC filter |\n   842→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/ProfileRoleService.java` | Role resolution with cache |\n   843→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/AuditLogService.java` | Audit logging |\n   844→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleEventService.java` | SSE event management |\n   845→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/service/RoleAssignmentService.java` | Role assignment ops |\n   846→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileClient.java` | Profile service client |\n   847→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/client/ProfileResponse.java` | Profile DTO |\n   848→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogEntity.java` | Audit entity |\n   849→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/persistence/AuditLogRepository.java` | Audit repository |\n   850→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacConfiguration.java` | Config class |\n   851→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/config/RbacProperties.java` | Properties record |\n   852→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/matcher/RbacPathMatcher.java` | Path matching |\n   853→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/rbac/controller/RoleEventsController.java` | SSE endpoint |\n   854→| `backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/rbac/db.changelog-rbac-001.yaml` | Audit table migration |\n   855→\n   856→### Modified Files (Backend)\n   857→\n   858→| Path | Changes |\n   859→|------|---------|\n   860→| `backend-mcp/build.gradle` | Add Caffeine cache (if not present) |\n   861→| `backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/McpApplication.java` | Add rbac package to scan |\n   862→\n   863→### New Files (Frontend)\n   864→\n   865→| Path | Purpose |\n   866→|------|---------|\n   867→| `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.ts` | Role guard hook with SSE |\n   868→| `frontend/src/components/RoleGuard.tsx` | Role guard component |\n   869→| `frontend/src/lib/useRoleGuard.test.ts` | Hook tests |\n   870→\n   871→### Modified Files (Frontend)\n   872→\n   873→| Path | Changes |\n   874→|------|---------|\n   875→| `frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts` | Add SSE subscription, roleVersion |\n   876→| `frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx` | Use useRoleGuard hook |\n   877→| `frontend/src/App.tsx` | Add RoleGuard for admin nav |\n   878→\n   879→---\n   880→\n   881→## Configuration\n   882→\n   883→### application-rbac.yaml\n   884→\n   885→```yaml\n   886→rbac:\n   887→  cache:\n   888→    ttl-minutes: 5\n   889→  protected-paths:\n   890→    - path: \"/api/notes/**\"\n   891→      methods: [\"POST\", \"PUT\", \"DELETE\"]\n   892→      required-roles: [\"user\", \"admin\"]\n   893→    - path: \"/api/admin/**\"\n   894→      methods: [\"*\"]\n   895→      required-roles: [\"admin\"]\n   896→  public-paths:\n   897→    - \"/actuator/health\"\n   898→    - \"/api/public/**\"\n   899→    - \"/api/profiles/role-events\"\n   900→\n   901→profile:\n   902→  service:\n   903→    url: ${PROFILE_SERVICE_URL:http://localhost:8081}\n   904→```\n   905→\n   906→---\n   907→\n   908→## Rollout Plan\n   909→\n   910→### Phase 1: Deploy Backend (Day 13)\n   911→1. Run database migration\n   912→2. Deploy RBAC filter in \"audit-only\" mode (log but don't block)\n   913→3. Monitor audit logs for 24 hours\n   914→\n   915→### Phase 2: Enable Enforcement (Day 14)\n   916→1. Switch RBAC filter to enforcement mode\n   917→2. Monitor 403 rates and latency\n   918→3. Verify cache hit rates\n   919→\n   920→### Phase 3: Frontend Deploy (Day 15)\n   921→1. Deploy updated frontend with SSE subscription\n   922→2. Monitor WebSocket connection rates\n   923→3. Verify role sync within 5 seconds\n   924→\n   925→### Rollback Plan\n   926→- Feature flag: `rbac.enforcement.enabled` (default: false)\n   927→- Quick disable via config change\n   928→- Audit logs preserved for analysis\n   929→\n   930→---\n   931→\n   932→## AIDD:ACCEPTANCE\n   933→\n   934→- [ ] AC-1: All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs return 403 for users without required roles\n   935→- [ ] AC-2: All role operations (GRANT/REVOKE/DENIED) logged to rbac_audit_log\n   936→- [ ] AC-3: Frontend role guards update within 5 seconds of backend change\n   937→- [ ] AC-4: RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms under 1000 RPS load\n   938→- [ ] AC-5: Zero breaking changes to existing public APIs\n   939→\n   940→---\n   941→\n   942→## AIDD:METRICS\n   943→\n   944→| Metric | Target | Measurement |\n   945→|--------|--------|-------------|\n   946→| RBAC latency P95 | ≤ 10ms | Micrometer timer on filter |\n   947→| Cache hit rate | ≥ 90% | Caffeine cache stats |\n   948→| Role sync delay | ≤ 5s | Frontend timestamp diff |\n   949→| Audit log coverage | 100% | Count vs request volume |\n   950→| 403 error rate | < 1% | HTTP status metrics |\n   951→\n   952→---\n   953→\n   954→## AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS\n   955→\n   956→None — all questions resolved via research findings.\n   957→\n   958→---\n   959→\n   960→## AIDD:READ_LOG\n   961→\n   962→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md`\n   963→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n   964→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n   965→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`\n   966→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileTypes.ts`\n   967→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts` (excerpt)\n   968→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx`\n   969→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/McpApplication.java`\n   970→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/notes/persistence/NoteEntity.java`\n   971→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/notes/db.changelog-master.yaml`\n   972→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/build.gradle`\n   973→\n   974→---\n   975→\n   976→## AIDD:ACTIONS_LOG\n   977→\n   978→- Created plan document with 5 phases\n   979→- Defined 19 new backend files\n   980→- Defined 3 new frontend files\n   981→- Specified 4 modified files\n   982→- Created database migration schema\n   983→- Documented SSE extension approach (vs WebSocket)\n   984→- Documented custom WebFlux filter approach (vs Spring Security)\n   985→\n   986→---\n   987→\n   988→## AIDD:VALIDATION_FEEDBACK\n   989→\n   990→**Validation Status:** WARN (executa