{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_LKGPI04UNrTKFMHfjc0Zmtlf","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Validation Report — TST-001 Implementation Plan\n     2→\n     3→**Status:** WARN\n     4→**Ticket:** TST-001\n     5→**Validated:** 2026-03-18\n     6→**Validator:** Plan Review Agent\n     7→\n     8→---\n     9→\n    10→## 1. Validation Summary\n    11→\n    12→| Category | Verdict | Notes |\n    13→|----------|---------|-------|\n    14→| **Overall** | **WARN** | Plan is executable with minor adjustments required |\n    15→| **Executability** | PASS | All tasks can be implemented with current codebase |\n    16→| **Dependencies** | PASS | Caffeine, WebFlux, SSE already available |\n    17→| **Research Alignment** | PASS | Correctly adapts PRD to actual codebase |\n    18→| **Risk Assessment** | WARN | 2 medium risks need mitigation planning |\n    19→\n    20→---\n    21→\n    22→## 2. Findings\n    23→\n    24→### 2.1 Positive Findings\n    25→\n    26→#### F1.1: Correct Technology Adaptations (PASS)\n    27→The plan correctly adapts PRD assumptions based on research findings:\n    28→\n    29→| PRD Assumption | Research Finding | Plan Adaptation | Status |\n    30→|----------------|------------------|-----------------|--------|\n    31→| JWT claims auth | X-Profile-Key header auth | Custom WebFlux filter | Correct |\n    32→| Redux state | Zustand with persistence | Extend Zustand store | Correct |\n    33→| WebSocket push | SSE already exists | Extend SSE infrastructure | Correct |\n    34→| Spring Security | Not in classpath | Custom WebFlux filters | Correct |\n    35→\n    36→#### F1.2: Dependencies Available (PASS)\n    37→All required dependencies are present in `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/build.gradle`:\n    38→\n    39→- **Caffeine cache**: Line 42 - `implementation \"com.github.ben-manes.caffeine:caffeine\"`\n    40→- **WebFlux**: Line 37 - `implementation \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-starter-webflux\"`\n    41→- **PostgreSQL**: Line 51 - `runtimeOnly \"org.postgresql:postgresql\"`\n    42→- **Liquibase**: Line 45 - `implementation \"org.liquibase:liquibase-core\"`\n    43→- **SSE Infrastructure**: Already implemented in `apiClient.ts:1427-1456`\n    44→\n    45→#### F1.3: Database Pattern Alignment (PASS)\n    46→The audit table migration follows existing patterns from `db.changelog-master.yaml`:\n    47→- Uses UUID primary keys with `gen_random_uuid()`\n    48→- Uses `TIMESTAMP WITH TIME ZONE` for timestamps\n    49→- Uses `JSONB` for flexible metadata\n    50→- Follows naming conventions (`user_namespace`, `user_reference`)\n    51→\n    52→#### F1.4: Frontend Integration Points Verified (PASS)\n    53→- Profile store uses Zustand with persistence (confirmed in `profileStore.ts:36-76`)\n    54→- Roles are stored as `string[]` in profile (confirmed in `profileTypes.ts:31`)\n    55→- Admin role check pattern exists (confirmed in `AdminRoles.tsx:34-36`)\n    56→- SSE infrastructure exists (confirmed in `apiClient.ts:1427-1456`)\n    57→\n    58→### 2.2 Issues and Concerns\n    59→\n    60→#### F2.1: Component Scan Configuration Missing (WARN)\n    61→**Location**: `McpApplication.java`\n    62→**Issue**: The plan mentions adding RBAC package to scan, but the application uses profile-based component scanning. The RBAC module needs to be added to ALL profiles or a new profile configuration created.\n    63→\n    64→**Current structure**:\n    65→```java\n    66→@SpringBootApplication(scanBasePackages = \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.config\")\n    67→@Import({\n    68→  McpApplication.InsightConfig.class,\n    69→  McpApplication.FlowOpsConfig.class,\n    70→  // ... etc\n    71→})\n    72→```\n    73→\n    74→**Recommendation**: Add RBAC to a shared/common configuration or create a base configuration class that all profiles extend.\n    75→\n    76→#### F2.2: Profile Service Integration Undefined (WARN)\n    77→**Location**: Phase 2 - Profile Service Integration\n    78→**Issue**: The plan assumes a `profileClient.fetchRoles(identity)` method exists, but there's no evidence of a profile service API in the codebase.\n    79→\n    80→**Evidence**: Research shows roles are stored in the profile document (`profileTypes.ts:31`), but no backend API for fetching profile roles by namespace/reference was found.\n    81→\n    82→**Recommendation**: Define the profile service contract or implement role lookup via existing database tables.\n    83→\n    84→#### F2.3: Missing RbacPathMatcher Implementation (WARN)\n    85→**Location**: Phase 1.3 - RBAC Filter\n    86→**Issue**: The plan references `RbacPathMatcher` but doesn't provide implementation details for path-to-role mapping.\n    87→\n    88→**Recommendation**: Add explicit path matching rules configuration to `application-rbac.yaml`.\n    89→\n    90→#### F2.4: Liquibase Context Configuration (INFO)\n    91→**Location**: Phase 1.1 - Database Migration\n    92→**Issue**: The migration uses `context: rbac` but there's no documentation on how contexts are activated in this project.\n    93→\n    94→**Recommendation**: Verify Liquibase context configuration in application properties.\n    95→\n    96→---\n    97→\n    98→## 3. Recommendations\n    99→\n   100→### R1: Add Shared RBAC Configuration (Required)\n   101→Create a base configuration that all profiles can import:\n   102→\n   103→```java\n   104→@Configuration\n   105→@Profile(\"!test\") // Active in all non-test profiles\n   106→@ComponentScan(basePackages = {\n   107→    \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac\",\n   108→    \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.config\"\n   109→})\n   110→@EnableConfigurationProperties(RbacProperties.class)\n   111→public class RbacConfig {\n   112→}\n   113→```\n   114→\n   115→### R2: Define Profile Service Contract (Required)\n   116→Add explicit API contract for profile role resolution:\n   117→\n   118→```java\n   119→// Option A: If profile service exists\n   120→@Value(\"${profile.service.url:http://localhost:8081}\")\n   121→private String profileServiceUrl;\n   122→\n   123→// Option B: If roles are in local database\n   124→// Add roles column to existing table or create rbac_profile_roles table\n   125→```\n   126→\n   127→### R3: Add Path Matcher Configuration (Required)\n   128→Complete the `RbacPathMatcher` implementation with explicit path rules:\n   129→\n   130→```java\n   131→@Component\n   132→public class RbacPathMatcher {\n   133→    private final RbacProperties properties;\n   134→    \n   135→    public Set<Role> getRequiredRoles(String path, HttpMethod method) {\n   136→        // Implement path pattern matching\n   137→        // Return empty set for public paths\n   138→        // Return required roles from configuration\n   139→    }\n   140→    \n   141→    public boolean isPublicPath(String path) {\n   142→        return properties.publicPaths().stream()\n   143→            .anyMatch(path::startsWith);\n   144→    }\n   145→}\n   146→```\n   147→\n   148→### R4: Add Feature Flag for Rollout (Recommended)\n   149→Add feature flag configuration for gradual rollout:\n   150→\n   151→```yaml\n   152→rbac:\n   153→  enforcement:\n   154→    enabled: false  # Start in audit-only mode\n   155→    mode: AUDIT_ONLY # AUDIT_ONLY or ENFORCE\n   156→```\n   157→\n   158→### R5: Cache Metrics Exposure (Recommended)\n   159→Add cache metrics for observability:\n   160→\n   161→```java\n   162→@Bean\n   163→public MeterBinder rbacCacheMetrics(ProfileRoleService roleService) {\n   164→    return registry -> Gauge.builder(\"rbac.cache.hit_rate\", \n   165→            () -> roleService.getCacheStats().hitRate())\n   166→        .register(registry);\n   167→}\n   168→```\n   169→\n   170→---\n   171→\n   172→## 4. Risk Register\n   173→\n   174→| Risk ID | Description | Probability | Impact | Status | Mitigation |\n   175→|---------|-------------|-------------|--------|--------|------------|\n   176→| R-001 | Profile service unavailable | Medium | High | Open | Circuit breaker; fail-closed; cache roles |\n   177→| R-002 | Cache stale roles after assignment | Medium | Medium | Open | Cache invalidation on role change; TTL 5min |\n   178→| R-003 | SSE connection memory leak | Low | Medium | Open | Proper cleanup on disconnect; subscriber map limits |\n   179→| R-004 | Audit log write failures | Low | Medium | Open | Async logging; error queue; never block request |\n   180→| R-005 | RBAC filter performance degradation | Low | High | Mitigated | Caffeine cache; async audit; P95 target 10ms |\n   181→| R-006 | Breaking change to existing APIs | Low | High | Mitigated | Feature flags; audit-only mode first; rollback plan |\n   182→| R-007 | Component scan misses RBAC beans | Medium | High | Open | Add to all profile configs; verify on startup |\n   183→| R-008 | Missing profile service integration | High | High | Open | Define contract; implement fallback to local DB |\n   184→\n   185→### Risk Details\n   186→\n   187→#### R-001: Profile Service Unavailable\n   188→**Scenario**: Profile service is down when RBAC filter needs to check roles.\n   189→**Impact**: All mutation APIs return 403 (fail-closed) or 500 (if unhandled).\n   190→**Mitigation**: \n   191→- Implement circuit breaker pattern\n   192→- Cache roles with 5-minute TTL\n   193→- Return cached roles during outage\n   194→- Log warning for cache-based decisions\n   195→\n   196→#### R-002: Cache Stale Roles\n   197→**Scenario**: Admin assigns new role, but user still gets 403 due to cached old roles.\n   198→**Impact**: User experience degradation; support tickets.\n   199→**Mitigation**:\n   200→- Cache invalidation on role assignment\n   201→- SSE notification triggers cache refresh\n   202→- Document 5-minute maximum delay\n   203→\n   204→#### R-007: Component Scan Misses RBAC Beans\n   205→**Scenario**: RBAC filter not registered due to missing component scan.\n   206→**Impact**: RBAC not enforced; security gap.\n   207→**Mitigation**:\n   208→- Add RBAC config to all profile configurations\n   209→- Add integration test verifying filter registration\n   210→- Log filter registration on startup\n   211→\n   212→#### R-008: Missing Profile Service Integration\n   213→**Scenario**: No API exists to fetch roles by profile key.\n   214→**Impact**: Cannot implement role resolution.\n   215→**Mitigation**:\n   216→- Verify profile service API exists\n   217→- If not, implement role storage in RBAC module\n   218→- Create migration for rbac_profile_roles table\n   219→\n   220→---\n   221→\n   222→## 5. Blockers\n   223→\n   224→No blockers identified. Plan can proceed with WARN-level issues addressed.\n   225→\n   226→---\n   227→\n   228→## 6. AIDD:READ_LOG\n   229→\n   230→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md`\n   231→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/reports/context/TST-001.pack.md`\n   232→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n   233→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n   234→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/build.gradle`\n   235→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/java/com/aiadvent/mcp/backend/McpApplication.java`\n   236→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/backend-mcp/src/main/resources/db/changelog/notes/db.changelog-master.yaml`\n   237→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`\n   238→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileTypes.ts`\n   239→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts`\n   240→- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx`\n   241→\n   242→---\n   243→\n   244→## 7. AIDD:ACTIONS_LOG\n   245→\n   246→- Validated plan executability against codebase\n   247→- Verified all dependencies present\n   248→- Confirmed research findings alignment\n   249→- Identified 2 WARN-level issues (component scan, profile service)\n   250→- Created risk register with 8 items\n   251→- Generated 5 recommendations\n   252→\n   253→---\n   254→\n   255→## 8. Next Actions\n   256→\n   257→1. **Address R-008**: Verify profile service API exists or implement local role storage\n   258→2. **Address R-007**: Add RBAC configuration to all profile configs in McpApplication.java\n   259→3. **Address F2.3**: Complete RbacPathMatcher implementation details\n   260→4. **Proceed to tasklist creation** once WARN items are resolved\n   261→\n   262→---\n   263→\n   264→## 9. Validation Checklist\n   265→\n   266→- [x] Plan document exists and is readable\n   267→- [x] All phases have clear goals and deliverables\n   268→- [x] Dependencies are available in codebase\n   269→- [x] Research findings are correctly incorporated\n   270→- [x] Non-negotiables are defined and measurable\n   271→- [x] Risks are identified with mitigations\n   272→- [x] Test strategy is defined\n   273→- [x] Rollback plan is documented\n   274→- [ ] WARN items addressed (pending)\n   275→\n   276→---\n   277→\n   278→**Status:** WARN - Plan is executable after addressing component scan and profile service integration issues.\n   279→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"tool_EkXO8SVVEnKyCVtVN2wxMhSx","session_id":"c9d8f772-fac0-4aa0-ba05-6715d2bcaffd","uuid":"71292b44-7345-4bb5-a6a4-d5f8096