{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_EkXO8SVVEnKyCVtVN2wxMhSx","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the information needed to provide a comprehensive plan review. Let me compile my findings.\n\n---\n\n## Plan Review Report — TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n\n### Overall Verdict: **WARN**\n\nThe implementation plan is well-structured and executable with minor adjustments required before implementation begins. The plan correctly adapts PRD assumptions to actual codebase findings.\n\n---\n\n### Key Findings\n\n| Finding ID | Description | Severity | Status |\n|------------|-------------|----------|--------|\n| F-001 | Correct technology adaptations from research | Positive | PASS |\n| F-002 | All dependencies verified available | Positive | PASS |\n| F-003 | Component scan configuration gap | Medium | WARN |\n| F-004 | Profile service integration undefined | Medium | WARN |\n| F-005 | Missing RbacPathMatcher implementation | Medium | WARN |\n| F-006 | Comprehensive test strategy defined | Positive | PASS |\n| F-007 | Rollout plan with feature flags included | Positive | PASS |\n\n---\n\n### Detailed Assessment\n\n#### 1. Milestones and Phases (PASS)\n\nThe plan defines 5 clear phases with realistic timelines:\n\n| Phase | Duration | Goal | Assessment |\n|-------|----------|------|------------|\n| Phase 1 | Days 1-3 | Backend Foundation | Well-defined; includes migration, filter, caching, audit |\n| Phase 2 | Days 4-5 | Profile Service Integration | Clear, but depends on resolving R-008 |\n| Phase 3 | Days 6-8 | Frontend Role Sync | Good SSE extension approach |\n| Phase 4 | Days 9-10 | SSE Role Events Endpoint | Proper reactive implementation |\n| Phase 5 | Days 11-12 | Testing & Validation | Comprehensive coverage |\n\n**Strengths:**\n- Logical dependency chain between phases\n- Each phase has concrete deliverables\n- Code examples provided for critical components\n\n#### 2. Dependency Chain (PASS with WARN)\n\n**Verified Dependencies:**\n- Caffeine cache: Available in build.gradle\n- WebFlux: Already in classpath\n- PostgreSQL + Liquibase: Confirmed\n- SSE infrastructure: Exists in frontend\n\n**Dependency Gaps:**\n- Profile service API contract not verified (R-008)\n- Component scan configuration needs update (R-007)\n\n#### 3. Integration Points (WARN)\n\n| Integration Point | Status | Issue |\n|-------------------|--------|-------|\n| RBAC Filter | Defined | Implementation clear |\n| Profile Service | Undefined | No API contract verified |\n| Audit Logging | Defined | Schema follows existing patterns |\n| Frontend SSE | Defined | Good reuse of existing infrastructure |\n| Component Scan | Missing | Needs RBAC package registration |\n\n#### 4. Testing Strategy (PASS)\n\nThe plan includes adequate test coverage:\n\n- **Unit Tests:** RBAC filter, role service, caching behavior\n- **Integration Tests:** End-to-end role change flow\n- **Performance Tests:** P95 latency validation\n- **Frontend Tests:** Hook behavior, role guard updates\n\n#### 5. PRD Alignment (PASS)\n\nThe plan correctly adapts PRD requirements to actual codebase:\n\n| PRD Requirement | Plan Adaptation | Correct |\n|-----------------|-----------------|---------|\n| JWT claims | X-Profile-Key headers | Yes |\n| Redux | Zustand extension | Yes |\n| WebSocket | SSE extension | Yes |\n| Spring Security | Custom WebFlux filters | Yes |\n\n---\n\n### Specific Recommendations\n\n#### R-001: Address Profile Service Integration (HIGH PRIORITY)\n\n**Issue:** The plan assumes `profileClient.fetchRoles()` exists, but no backend API was found in research.\n\n**Recommendation:**\n```java\n// Option A: Verify and document existing profile service API\n// Option B: Add local role storage if no service exists\n\n// Add to Phase 1.1 migration:\n- changeSet:\n    id: rbac-0002-profile-roles\n    changes:\n      - createTable:\n          tableName: rbac_profile_roles\n          columns:\n            - column: { name: profile_namespace, type: VARCHAR(32) }\n            - column: { name: profile_reference, type: VARCHAR(128) }\n            - column: { name: role, type: VARCHAR(32) }\n```\n\n#### R-002: Complete Component Scan Configuration (HIGH PRIORITY)\n\n**Issue:** RBAC beans may not be registered due to profile-based component scanning.\n\n**Recommendation:**\nAdd to `McpApplication.java` or create `RbacConfig.java`:\n```java\n@Configuration\n@Profile(\"!test\")\n@ComponentScan(basePackages = \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac\")\npublic class RbacConfig {\n}\n```\n\n#### R-003: Add RbacPathMatcher Implementation (MEDIUM PRIORITY)\n\n**Issue:** Referenced in filter but implementation not detailed.\n\n**Recommendation:**\nAdd explicit implementation in Phase 1.6 with configuration-driven path rules.\n\n#### R-004: Add Feature Flag Verification (MEDIUM PRIORITY)\n\n**Issue:** Feature flags mentioned but not integrated into filter logic.\n\n**Recommendation:**\nUpdate `RbacWebFilter` to support audit-only mode:\n```java\nif (!rbacProperties.enforcement().enabled()) {\n    // Log but don't block\n    return chain.filter(exchange);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Risk Register Summary\n\n| Risk | Probability | Impact | Status |\n|------|-------------|--------|--------|\n| Profile service unavailable | Medium | High | Needs circuit breaker |\n| Cache stale roles | Medium | Medium | Acceptable with 5min TTL |\n| Component scan misses beans | Medium | High | **Must fix before deploy** |\n| Missing profile service API | High | High | **Must verify before Phase 2** |\n| SSE memory leak | Low | Medium | Monitor with subscriber limits |\n\n---\n\n### Action Items for Implementation\n\n| Action | Priority | Owner | Phase |\n|--------|----------|-------|-------|\n| Verify profile service API or implement local roles | HIGH | Implementer | Before Phase 2 |\n| Add RBAC config to McpApplication.java | HIGH | Implementer | Phase 1 |\n| Complete RbacPathMatcher implementation | MEDIUM | Implementer | Phase 1 |\n| Add feature flag integration to filter | MEDIUM | Implementer | Phase 1 |\n| Add cache metrics exposure | LOW | Implementer | Phase 5 |\n\n---\n\n### Final Assessment\n\n**Status:** WARN (executable after addressing WARN items)\n\nThe plan is comprehensive and technically sound. The 3 WARN-level items (component scan, profile service integration, path matcher) should be resolved before or during Phase 1 implementation. No blockers prevent implementation from proceeding.\n\n**Recommended Next Actions:**\n1. Resolve R-008: Verify profile service API exists or implement local role storage\n2. Resolve R-007: Add RBAC configuration to component scan\n3. Proceed to tasklist creation and implementation\n\n---\n\n**AIDD:READ_LOG:**\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001-validation.md`\n\n**AIDD:ACTIONS_LOG:**\n- Reviewed PRD requirements and research findings\n- Analyzed implementation plan structure and phases\n- Identified 3 WARN-level issues requiring attention\n- Validated dependency availability and integration points\n- Confirmed test strategy adequacy\n- Documented specific recommendations for plan improvements"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aec3e98061822a9ea (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 37009\ntool_uses: 6\nduration_ms: 89901</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9d8f772-fac0-4aa0-ba05-6715d2bcaffd","uuid":"8d462f0c-8aa0-469c-b568-f0b47764cd79","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"You are a plan-reviewer subagent. Review the implementation plan and PRD for ticket TST-001.\n\nCONTEXT:\n- Ticket: TST-001\n- Slug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\n- PRD Path: aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\n- Research Path: aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md\n\nTASK:\n1. Read the PRD file at aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\n2. Read the research file at aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md (if exists)\n3. Review the implementation plan sections (milestones, phases, automation/checks)\n4. Identify any executable risks or blockers in the plan\n\nFOCUS AREAS:\n- Are the milestones realistic and well-defined?\n- Is there a clear dependency chain between phases?\n- Are there missing integration points?\n- Are the testing/validation strategies adequate?\n- Do the phases align with the PRD requirements?\n\nOUTPUT:\nProvide a structured review report with:\n- Overall verdict (PASS / WARN / BLOCK)\n- Key findings with severity\n- Specific recommendations for plan improvements","agentId":"aec3e98061822a9ea","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now I have all the information needed to provide a comprehensive plan review. Let me compile my findings.\n\n---\n\n## Plan Review Report — TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n\n### Overall Verdict: **WARN**\n\nThe implementation plan is well-structured and executable with minor adjustments required before implementation begins. The plan correctly adapts PRD assumptions to actual codebase findings.\n\n---\n\n### Key Findings\n\n| Finding ID | Description | Severity | Status |\n|------------|-------------|----------|--------|\n| F-001 | Correct technology adaptations from research | Positive | PASS |\n| F-002 | All dependencies verified available | Positive | PASS |\n| F-003 | Component scan configuration gap | Medium | WARN |\n| F-004 | Profile service integration undefined | Medium | WARN |\n| F-005 | Missing RbacPathMatcher implementation | Medium | WARN |\n| F-006 | Comprehensive test strategy defined | Positive | PASS |\n| F-007 | Rollout plan with feature flags included | Positive | PASS |\n\n---\n\n### Detailed Assessment\n\n#### 1. Milestones and Phases (PASS)\n\nThe plan defines 5 clear phases with realistic timelines:\n\n| Phase | Duration | Goal | Assessment |\n|-------|----------|------|------------|\n| Phase 1 | Days 1-3 | Backend Foundation | Well-defined; includes migration, filter, caching, audit |\n| Phase 2 | Days 4-5 | Profile Service Integration | Clear, but depends on resolving R-008 |\n| Phase 3 | Days 6-8 | Frontend Role Sync | Good SSE extension approach |\n| Phase 4 | Days 9-10 | SSE Role Events Endpoint | Proper reactive implementation |\n| Phase 5 | Days 11-12 | Testing & Validation | Comprehensive coverage |\n\n**Strengths:**\n- Logical dependency chain between phases\n- Each phase has concrete deliverables\n- Code examples provided for critical components\n\n#### 2. Dependency Chain (PASS with WARN)\n\n**Verified Dependencies:**\n- Caffeine cache: Available in build.gradle\n- WebFlux: Already in classpath\n- PostgreSQL + Liquibase: Confirmed\n- SSE infrastructure: Exists in frontend\n\n**Dependency Gaps:**\n- Profile service API contract not verified (R-008)\n- Component scan configuration needs update (R-007)\n\n#### 3. Integration Points (WARN)\n\n| Integration Point | Status | Issue |\n|-------------------|--------|-------|\n| RBAC Filter | Defined | Implementation clear |\n| Profile Service | Undefined | No API contract verified |\n| Audit Logging | Defined | Schema follows existing patterns |\n| Frontend SSE | Defined | Good reuse of existing infrastructure |\n| Component Scan | Missing | Needs RBAC package registration |\n\n#### 4. Testing Strategy (PASS)\n\nThe plan includes adequate test coverage:\n\n- **Unit Tests:** RBAC filter, role service, caching behavior\n- **Integration Tests:** End-to-end role change flow\n- **Performance Tests:** P95 latency validation\n- **Frontend Tests:** Hook behavior, role guard updates\n\n#### 5. PRD Alignment (PASS)\n\nThe plan correctly adapts PRD requirements to actual codebase:\n\n| PRD Requirement | Plan Adaptation | Correct |\n|-----------------|-----------------|---------|\n| JWT claims | X-Profile-Key headers | Yes |\n| Redux | Zustand extension | Yes |\n| WebSocket | SSE extension | Yes |\n| Spring Security | Custom WebFlux filters | Yes |\n\n---\n\n### Specific Recommendations\n\n#### R-001: Address Profile Service Integration (HIGH PRIORITY)\n\n**Issue:** The plan assumes `profileClient.fetchRoles()` exists, but no backend API was found in research.\n\n**Recommendation:**\n```java\n// Option A: Verify and document existing profile service API\n// Option B: Add local role storage if no service exists\n\n// Add to Phase 1.1 migration:\n- changeSet:\n    id: rbac-0002-profile-roles\n    changes:\n      - createTable:\n          tableName: rbac_profile_roles\n          columns:\n            - column: { name: profile_namespace, type: VARCHAR(32) }\n            - column: { name: profile_reference, type: VARCHAR(128) }\n            - column: { name: role, type: VARCHAR(32) }\n```\n\n#### R-002: Complete Component Scan Configuration (HIGH PRIORITY)\n\n**Issue:** RBAC beans may not be registered due to profile-based component scanning.\n\n**Recommendation:**\nAdd to `McpApplication.java` or create `RbacConfig.java`:\n```java\n@Configuration\n@Profile(\"!test\")\n@ComponentScan(basePackages = \"com.aiadvent.mcp.backend.rbac\")\npublic class RbacConfig {\n}\n```\n\n#### R-003: Add RbacPathMatcher Implementation (MEDIUM PRIORITY)\n\n**Issue:** Referenced in filter but implementation not detailed.\n\n**Recommendation:**\nAdd explicit implementation in Phase 1.6 with configuration-driven path rules.\n\n#### R-004: Add Feature Flag Verification (MEDIUM PRIORITY)\n\n**Issue:** Feature flags mentioned but not integrated into filter logic.\n\n**Recommendation:**\nUpdate `RbacWebFilter` to support audit-only mode:\n```java\nif (!rbacProperties.enforcement().enabled()) {\n    // Log but don't block\n    return chain.filter(exchange);\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Risk Register Summary\n\n| Risk | Probability | Impact | Status |\n|------|-------------|--------|--------|\n| Profile service unavailable | Medium | High | Needs circuit breaker |\n| Cache stale roles | Medium | Medium | Acceptable with 5min TTL |\n| Component scan misses beans | Medium | High | **Must fix before deploy** |\n| Missing profile service API | High | High | **Must verify before Phase 2** |\n| SSE memory leak | Low | Medium | Monitor with subscriber limits |\n\n---\n\n### Action Items for Implementation\n\n| Action | Priority | Owner | Phase |\n|--------|----------|-------|-------|\n| Verify profile service API or implement local roles | HIGH | Implementer | Before Phase 2 |\n| Add RBAC config to McpApplication.java | HIGH | Implementer | Phase 1 |\n| Complete RbacPathMatcher implementation | MEDIUM | Implementer | Phase 1 |\n| Add feature flag integration to filter | MEDIUM | Implementer | Phase 1 |\n| Add cache metrics exposure | LOW | Implementer | Phase 5 |\n\n---\n\n### Final Assessment\n\n**Status:** WARN (executable after addressing WARN items)\n\nThe plan is comprehensive and technically sound. The 3 WARN-level items (component scan, profile service integration, path matcher) should be resolved before or during Phase 1 implementation. No blockers prevent implementation from proceeding.\n\n**Recommended Next Actions:**\n1. Resolve R-008: Verify profile service API exists or implement local role storage\n2. Resolve R-007: Add RBAC configuration to component scan\n3. Proceed to tasklist creation and implementation\n\n---\n\n**AIDD:READ_LOG:**\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md`\n- `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/plan/TST-001-validation.md`\n\n**AIDD:ACTIONS_LOG:**\n- Reviewed PRD requirements and research findings\n- Analyzed implementation plan structure and phases\n- Identified 3 WARN-level issues requiring attention\n- Validated dependency availability and integration points\n- Confirmed test strategy adequacy\n- Documented specific recommendations for plan improvements"}],"totalDurationMs":89901,"totalTokens":37009,"totalToolUseCount":6,"usage":{"input_tokens":4174,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":31232,"output_tokens":1603,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"msg_nlfRRy9quTTPLio0xKQyLw9m","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"tool_XB0hYZ0ZrKGANn0QCivqAPuB","name":"Edit","input":{"replace_all":false,"file_path":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md","old_string":"## 11. PRD Review\nStatus: PENDING\n\n### Summary\n- `<Ключевые выводы ревью>`\n\n### Findings\n- [ ] `<Описание проблемы>` — `<Серьёзность>` — `<Рекомендация>`\n\n### Action items\n- [ ] `<Действие>` — `<Ответственный>` — `<Дедлайн>`\n\n> Обновите статус на `READY`, когда все пункты закрыты.","new_string":"## 11. PRD Review\nStatus: NOT_READY\n\n### Summary\nPRD contains critical inconsistencies between analyst answers (Q1-Q5) and research findings. The PRD assumes JWT-claims middleware and Redux, but research shows the system uses X-Profile-Key header auth and Zustand. These mismatches will cause implementation failures if not resolved.\n\n### Findings\n- [ ] **F1: Auth Model Mismatch** — **BLOCKER** — PRD states \"JWT-claims middleware\" (Q2=B) but research shows system uses X-Profile-Key and X-Profile-Auth headers, not JWT. PRD section 2 and AIDD:DECISIONS incorrectly reference JWT.\n- [ ] **F2: Frontend State Management Mismatch** — **BLOCKER** — PRD states \"React + Context/Redux\" (Q3=A) but research shows frontend uses Zustand with persistence, not Redux.\n- [ ] **F3: Real-time Infrastructure Mismatch** — **HIGH** — PRD requires WebSocket (Q5=A) but research shows SSE already exists and is used for flows/MCP. Need to evaluate SSE vs WebSocket decision.\n- [ ] **F4: Research Status Warning** — **MEDIUM** — Research report shows Status: warn with open questions about Spring Security, JWT, and WebSocket that conflict with PRD decisions.\n- [ ] **F5: AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS Not Cleared** — **MEDIUM** — PRD section AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS is empty, but research shows 3 unresolved questions (Q1-Q3 in research) about implementation approach.\n- [ ] **F6: AIDD:ROLL_OUT Empty** — **LOW** — Rollout plan section is a placeholder with no actual content.\n- [ ] **F7: Research Hints Not Validated** — **MEDIUM** — AIDD:RESEARCH_HINTS lists paths like `src/middleware:src/auth` but research found no existing security configuration at these paths.\n\n### Action items\n- [ ] **AI-1: Update Q2 answer** — **Analyst** — Change Q2 from \"JWT-claims middleware\" to \"X-Profile-Key header-based auth\" to match actual system architecture.\n- [ ] **AI-2: Update Q3 answer** — **Analyst** — Change Q3 from \"Redux\" to \"Zustand\" to match actual frontend state management.\n- [ ] **AI-3: Revisit Q5 decision** — **Analyst/Architect** — Evaluate using existing SSE infrastructure vs implementing new WebSocket for role sync.\n- [ ] **AI-4: Sync research findings** — **Researcher** — Close research open questions Q1-Q3 after PRD decisions are updated.\n- [ ] **AI-5: Fill rollout plan** — **Analyst** — Add rollout phases, feature flags, and rollback strategy to AIDD:ROLL_OUT section.\n- [ ] **AI-6: Update PRD sections** — **Analyst** — Synchronize all PRD sections (2, 6, 7, 8) with corrected Q1-Q5 answers.\n\n> Обновите статус на `READY`, когда все пункты закрыты."}}],"model":"kimi-for-coding","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":17067,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available","prompt_tokens":17067,"cached_tokens":0},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":"tool_FOjIvCGFFEWnRI2bMtf99ZbW","session_id":"c9d8f772-fac0-4aa0-ba05-6715d2bcaffd","uuid":"ee0746c9-77b1-4260-bedc-7b6e25c775fb"}
