{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_w7w1ylBcJFGjCqybfMfUvWyc","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Research Summary — TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n     2→\n     3→Status: warn\n     4→Last reviewed: 2026-03-18\n     5→Ticket: TST-001\n     6→Slug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\n     7→\n     8→## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK\n     9→- TBD\n    10→- Limit: <= 20 lines / <= 1200 chars.\n    11→- Paths discovered: none\n    12→- Invalid paths: none\n    13→- Pack-first: используйте `*-rlm.pack.*` и `rlm-slice`; не вставляйте raw JSONL.\n    14→\n    15→## AIDD:PRD_OVERRIDES\n    16→- none\n    17→## AIDD:NON_NEGOTIABLES\n    18→- All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs must enforce RBAC with 403 on violations\n    19→- Role operations (GRANT/REVOKE) must be auditable with timestamp, user, action\n    20→- Frontend role guards must update within 5 seconds of session change\n    21→- RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms\n    22→\n    23→## AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS\n    24→- Q1: Should RBAC be implemented as Spring Security filters or custom middleware? (Spring Security not currently in classpath)\n    25→- Q2: How to handle profile-to-role mapping given current header-based auth (no JWT)?\n    26→- Q3: Should WebSocket be introduced or extend existing SSE infrastructure for role sync?\n    27→\n    28→## AIDD:RISKS\n    29→| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n    30→|------|--------|------------|\n    31→| No Spring Security in current classpath | High | Add spring-boot-starter-security dependency |\n    32→| No JWT infrastructure exists | Medium | Implement custom RBAC based on profile roles from header |\n    33→| Profile auth uses custom headers not JWT claims | Medium | Adapt RBAC to use X-Profile-Key header for identity |\n    34→| SSE exists but PRD requires WebSocket | Low | Evaluate SSE for role push or implement WebSocket |\n    35→| Database schema has no audit_log table | Medium | Create new migration for audit_log table |\n    36→\n    37→## AIDD:DECISIONS\n    38→- **Auth Model**: Current system uses X-Profile-Key and X-Profile-Auth headers, not JWT\n    39→- **State Management**: Frontend uses Zustand (not Redux) with persistence\n    40→- **Real-time**: SSE already implemented for flows/MCP; WebSocket needs new infrastructure\n    41→- **Role Storage**: Roles stored in profile document (see profileTypes.ts: `roles: z.array(z.string())`)\n    42→\n    43→## AIDD:INTEGRATION_POINTS\n    44→\n    45→### Backend Integration Points\n    46→\n    47→1. **Profile Header Extraction** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts:92-110`)\n    48→   - `buildActiveProfileHeaders()` creates headers: X-Profile-Key, X-Profile-Channel, X-Profile-Auth\n    49→   - Backend must read these headers for identity\n    50→\n    51→2. **API Client** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts`)\n    52→   - All API calls use `buildActiveProfileHeaders()` for authentication\n    53→   - Admin role APIs: `fetchAdminProfiles()`, `assignProfileRole()`, `revokeProfileRole()`\n    54→\n    55→3. **No Existing Security Configuration**\n    56→   - No SecurityConfig, JWT, or @PreAuthorize annotations found\n    57→   - No spring-boot-starter-security in build.gradle\n    58→\n    59→### Frontend Integration Points\n    60→\n    61→1. **Profile Store** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`)\n    62→   - Uses Zustand with persistence\n    63→   - Profile document includes `roles: string[]`\n    64→   - Admin check: `state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin')`\n    65→\n    66→2. **Admin Role Guard** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx:34-36`)\n    67→   ```typescript\n    68→   const hasAdminRole = useProfileStore(\n    69→     (state) => !!state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin'),\n    70→   );\n    71→   ```\n    72→\n    73→3. **Route Guard** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/App.tsx:41-45`)\n    74→   ```typescript\n    75→   {hasAdminRole && (\n    76→     <NavLink to=\"/admin/roles\" className=\"nav-link\">\n    77→       Admin\n    78→     </NavLink>\n    79→   )}\n    80→   ```\n    81→\n    82→4. **SSE Infrastructure** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts`)\n    83→   - `subscribeToFlowEvents()` uses EventSource for real-time updates\n    84→   - Could be extended for role change notifications\n    85→\n    86→## AIDD:REUSE_CANDIDATES\n    87→\n    88→1. **Profile Header Parsing**\n    89→   - Location: `buildActiveProfileHeaders()` in `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts:92-110`\n    90→   - Reuse: Backend should implement similar header parsing for identity extraction\n    91→\n    92→2. **Role Check Pattern**\n    93→   - Location: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx:34-36`\n    94→   - Pattern: `state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin')`\n    95→   - Reuse: Standardize role check utility\n    96→\n    97→3. **Audit Event Types**\n    98→   - Location: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/components/ActiveProfileBanner.tsx:77-95`\n    99→   - Events: 'profile_created', 'profile_updated', 'identity_attached', 'identity_detached', 'role_assigned', 'role_revoked'\n   100→   - Reuse: Extend for RBAC audit events\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"c9d8f772-fac0-4aa0-ba05-6715d2bcaffd","uuid":"865701f1-46e2-4af7-a704-ccd649d62741","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/research/TST-001.md","content":"# Research Summary — TST-001: FS-RBAC-03 Live RBAC Enforcement\n\nStatus: warn\nLast reviewed: 2026-03-18\nTicket: TST-001\nSlug: fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\n\n## AIDD:CONTEXT_PACK\n- TBD\n- Limit: <= 20 lines / <= 1200 chars.\n- Paths discovered: none\n- Invalid paths: none\n- Pack-first: используйте `*-rlm.pack.*` и `rlm-slice`; не вставляйте raw JSONL.\n\n## AIDD:PRD_OVERRIDES\n- none\n## AIDD:NON_NEGOTIABLES\n- All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs must enforce RBAC with 403 on violations\n- Role operations (GRANT/REVOKE) must be auditable with timestamp, user, action\n- Frontend role guards must update within 5 seconds of session change\n- RBAC check latency P95 ≤ 10ms\n\n## AIDD:OPEN_QUESTIONS\n- Q1: Should RBAC be implemented as Spring Security filters or custom middleware? (Spring Security not currently in classpath)\n- Q2: How to handle profile-to-role mapping given current header-based auth (no JWT)?\n- Q3: Should WebSocket be introduced or extend existing SSE infrastructure for role sync?\n\n## AIDD:RISKS\n| Risk | Impact | Mitigation |\n|------|--------|------------|\n| No Spring Security in current classpath | High | Add spring-boot-starter-security dependency |\n| No JWT infrastructure exists | Medium | Implement custom RBAC based on profile roles from header |\n| Profile auth uses custom headers not JWT claims | Medium | Adapt RBAC to use X-Profile-Key header for identity |\n| SSE exists but PRD requires WebSocket | Low | Evaluate SSE for role push or implement WebSocket |\n| Database schema has no audit_log table | Medium | Create new migration for audit_log table |\n\n## AIDD:DECISIONS\n- **Auth Model**: Current system uses X-Profile-Key and X-Profile-Auth headers, not JWT\n- **State Management**: Frontend uses Zustand (not Redux) with persistence\n- **Real-time**: SSE already implemented for flows/MCP; WebSocket needs new infrastructure\n- **Role Storage**: Roles stored in profile document (see profileTypes.ts: `roles: z.array(z.string())`)\n\n## AIDD:INTEGRATION_POINTS\n\n### Backend Integration Points\n\n1. **Profile Header Extraction** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts:92-110`)\n   - `buildActiveProfileHeaders()` creates headers: X-Profile-Key, X-Profile-Channel, X-Profile-Auth\n   - Backend must read these headers for identity\n\n2. **API Client** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts`)\n   - All API calls use `buildActiveProfileHeaders()` for authentication\n   - Admin role APIs: `fetchAdminProfiles()`, `assignProfileRole()`, `revokeProfileRole()`\n\n3. **No Existing Security Configuration**\n   - No SecurityConfig, JWT, or @PreAuthorize annotations found\n   - No spring-boot-starter-security in build.gradle\n\n### Frontend Integration Points\n\n1. **Profile Store** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts`)\n   - Uses Zustand with persistence\n   - Profile document includes `roles: string[]`\n   - Admin check: `state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin')`\n\n2. **Admin Role Guard** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx:34-36`)\n   ```typescript\n   const hasAdminRole = useProfileStore(\n     (state) => !!state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin'),\n   );\n   ```\n\n3. **Route Guard** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/App.tsx:41-45`)\n   ```typescript\n   {hasAdminRole && (\n     <NavLink to=\"/admin/roles\" className=\"nav-link\">\n       Admin\n     </NavLink>\n   )}\n   ```\n\n4. **SSE Infrastructure** (`/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/apiClient.ts`)\n   - `subscribeToFlowEvents()` uses EventSource for real-time updates\n   - Could be extended for role change notifications\n\n## AIDD:REUSE_CANDIDATES\n\n1. **Profile Header Parsing**\n   - Location: `buildActiveProfileHeaders()` in `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/lib/profileStore.ts:92-110`\n   - Reuse: Backend should implement similar header parsing for identity extraction\n\n2. **Role Check Pattern**\n   - Location: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/pages/AdminRoles.tsx:34-36`\n   - Pattern: `state.profile?.roles?.some((role) => role === 'admin')`\n   - Reuse: Standardize role check utility\n\n3. **Audit Event Types**\n   - Location: `/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/frontend/src/components/ActiveProfileBanner.tsx:77-95`\n   - Events: 'profile_created', 'profile_updated', 'identity_attached', 'identity_detached', 'role_assigned', 'role_revoked'\n   - Reuse: Extend for RBAC audit events","numLines":100,"startLine":1,"totalLines":280}}}
